translate ru NeitherPath7_91ebb47d:
    # "Marion stumbles around, expecting a betrayal that never comes."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_4deafeba:
    # s "You have until the end of next day."
    s ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_dd2bfbc8:
    # s "After that, every soldier or peasant will be given free reign to kill you on sight, and paid handsomely if they do."
    s ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_5fd942e7:
    # "Marion doesn't speak, he only turns and runs."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_0994f858:
    # "Sarah would later learn that he took a remaining horse from the stables and rode out towards the border with Normandi."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_6fc2d573:
    # "After that, no more news came."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_63f7ff56:
    # "The war had been won, and Sarah cared little for Marion anymore."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_7cfd3686:
    # "Without his family, his base of support, his resources, he was just a man. Clever, ambitious, but just one man. Let him live out his days on the edge of the world."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_99078d81:
    # "Her army looted the ancestral home of the Achillea family, bringing home great coffers of gold, artifacts and relics to Castle Reinmeer."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_9ca6e8c3:
    # "Even with the share of the loot that dissapeared into the pockets of soldiers, the Rose family found their fortunes greatly expanded."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_bf7050da:
    # "On the road back to Castle Reinmeer, Sarah did not let Thomas go from her sight."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_d2379fbc:
    # "Riding in the wagon with her, he told her of his experience in the dungeon. His hand was missing a finger which spoke enough of his trials."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_d47ab7ba:
    # "Still, for as much as Thomas told Sarah, she knew her brother well enough that he was also keeping much more from her."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_bc43ca4d:
    # "At nights, on the road back home, she would find him tossing and turning in his sleep. He spoke often, screamed even."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_cf469e52:
    # "The tortures that he had suffered had left marks on his body as well as his mind."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_bcb4245e:
    # "Sarah feared only those of the body would heal any time soon."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_375b8ee9:
    # "Only when Sarah watched her brother step into Castle Reinmeer, did she finally feel truly safe again."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_7e0a2c4a:
    # "In the months that followed, Sarah did her best to support her brother, but though his withered body regained its strength, he remained forever changed."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_655fe09c:
    # "Her brother survived by retreating. Retreating from the outside world, and partially even from himself."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_b8dde0ca:
    # "Thomas became more like the young boy she had known her brother to be. Distant, lost in books, detached."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_e95bc51d:
    # "As the burdens of rule fell evermore to Sarah, she did not complain. She would have gladly done anything to relieve him of his burdens."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_bbd59ff4:
    # "In the end, it was Thomas who spoke of it first."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_f6c8075e:
    # "Both realized the realm could not thrive with a king who was no king, and so her brother proposed that she replace him."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_b03c2915:
    # "Sarah never wanted the crown for herself, but she accepted the role of regent, to rule in his stead until the day he would be better, though both feared such a day would never come."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_9266afa8:
    # "Once regent, Sarah took control of her nation's government in all but name, and her brother abandoned what last few tasks he still did, dissapearing entirely into his room and the royal libraries."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_f429dbbf:
    # "Much damage had been caused by both the invasion of the tribesmen and the uprising of the old houses."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_3dfa358d:
    # "Sarah took it upon herself to heal these wounds as best she could."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_79e397b0:
    # "The border provinces were reinforced, making sure that no future tribesmen army could strike at the heart of her country again."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_5673133a:
    # "The old houses were dealt with in their own way."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_5e6b7aca:
    # "Some, like the Achillea family, all but vanished from existence, their homes and properties seized, their family members hunted."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_98ba2419:
    # "For others, like the Highfield family, all those that bore the most guilt were strung from the gallows, but the smaller branches were allowed to live."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_28fa8855:
    # "Lily Highfield was promoted to head of her family, seizing control of the estate, ensuring there would always be a loyal head to one of the old houses."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_851044f2:
    # "In the end, though the old houses still existed in some fashion, their power was forever broken by Sarah, ensuring they could never rise up against her family."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_b7c66906:
    # "Varga, her warmaster, stood by Sarah as loyal as anyone could be."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_3e3198df:
    # "He travelled on her behalf across the nation, serving as her harder hand for when her soft touch failed to convince."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_ca63eca8:
    # "But with Sarah's skillful guidance, her nation fell into a soft and easy peace, as had existed for many years under her father."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_e72d162a:
    # "The ravages of war were put behind them and Rosanna flourished."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_f538a0a0:
    # "With its economy back on track, the nation soon began overtaking even many of its neighbours."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_d47065bd:
    # "While the old system of nobility continued to exist, new laws granted greater rights to citizens of all classes."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_153484ee:
    # "In time, Rosanna became a destination for scholars from around the world, attracted to the freedoms offered by its government."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_97d0637e:
    # "Sarah was present when the nation's first university, the Rose University, was officially opened."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_a575c42b:
    # "From across the world, stories of troubles came to them, such as the fall of old Bagrad. But Rosanna was spared, becoming a safe haven in an unsafe world."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_f3b82a45:
    # "As the peace settled and the nation gathered around its new regent, there was less and less need of Varga's more forceful hand."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_b1e04163:
    # "And so it was that five years passed."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_6a184d9d:
    # "Returning to Castle Reinmeer, Sarah brings her brother's body with her."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_ed93f464:
    # "She does not leave his side for the entire voyage back home."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_add2876a:
    # "When they arrive, the news is pronounced and the capitol enters a month of mourning, ordering all festivities and music silenced."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_21a6a88b:
    # "During the funeral of her brother, when he is placed in the family grave next to her father and mother, Sarah leans on Lady Carolyn."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_0bf005a4:
    # "During the funeral of her brother, when he is placed in the family grave next to her father and mother, Sarah leans on Lily."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_a8510216:
    # "During the funeral of her brother, when he is placed in the family grave next to her father and mother, Sarah stands by herself, alone."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_d5c63071:
    # "Once queen, Sarah assumes control of her nation's government."
    ""

translate ru NeitherPath7_f429dbbf_1:
